<TEXT>
   Ralph G. Reichhold, 94, a retired artist and
writer for The Pittsburgh Press, died Monday at the Courtland Manor
Nursing Home.
   Reichhold's editorial cartoons appeared in national magazines. He
created cartoon character Donald Dingbat, a tiny weatherbird that
appeared with the newspaper's daily weather forecasts for 37 years.
He also drew a panel comic for the newspaper.
   Reichhold worked for The Pittsburgh Press for 42 years and
retired in 1955.
