<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nick Virgilio, a New Jersey master of Japanese
haiku poetry, died Tuesday after suffering an apparent heart attack
while taping a television interview. He was 60.
   Phil O'Connor, senior ``Nightwatch'' producer, said CBS does not
plan to air the interview.
   Haiku, an unrhymed type of poetry, has three lines that usually
contain five, seven and five syllables, respectively. Virgilio's
poetry earned him admirers worldwide, according to The Courier-Post.
His celebrated ``Lily'' poem was translated by the crown prince of
Japan.
