<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pianist Victor Borge, the mirthful maestro who
has entertained millions with his blend of music and comedy,
celebrated his 80th birthday on the Caribbean island of St. Croix
with his wife, Sanna, and family.
   ``We have all the children and the in-laws and the grandchildren
in the house here, 20 in all,'' he said by telephone Tuesday.
``Everything is just dandy.
   ``I have, from all over the world, received congratulatory
messages and flowers _ the house is like a hothouse. It's very
charming and exciting and touching.''
   The Great Dane, who gained worldwide fame by punctuating his
virtuoso piano playing with punchlines, was asked about the secret
to his longevity.
   ``That I'm not dead,'' he replied.
   More seriously, he said, ``I think it's in the genes. Just good
luck, perhaps. My grandmother was 102 years old, my father 85, some
of his brothers 95, 92.''
   Borge added that he still has the energy to do his quota of 75 to
80 concerts a year around the world.
   ``That has not changed whatsoever,'' he said. ``It's like a tree
that grows and grows, and every year the fruit appears. And I just
pick the fruit.''
