Medellin, the second-largest city in Colombia. Their ages and U.S.
hometowns were not available.
   Pardo said the incident in La Florida, 180 miles southwest of
Bogota, took place during a religious service but did not specify
where it took place.
   He said the kidnappers also shouted slogans against the
extradition of Ledher Rivas, who was arrested and sent to the United
States in 1987 after a gun battle at his mansion in Medellin.
