lounge, has closed its doors.
   The last guests bid farewell Tuesday to the 68-year-old Wilshire
Boulevard landmark. In May, the owners, the J. Myer Schine family,
closed about three-quarters of the 500 rooms because they failed to
meet fire standards, and more than $1 million was needed for
earthquake-safety improvements.
</TEXT>
